		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There's <a href="http://www.acc.umu.se/~bosse/" class="postlink">FileDisk</a>, which turns an IMG file into a drive letter, but you need to invoke that program from the command prompt.<br /><br />If you need to make a new disk image, just make a large blank file, mount it with FileDisk, format it as FAT16, and dump on your files.</div>
<br />
<br />yep, FileDisk is probably the best option if you insist on free. i use WinImage though, it's the best choice on windows imo. and really, it is essentially free as long as you dont mind a quick nag screen when you start it. it doesn't expire.
<br />
<br />my WinImage nag screen now shows that the program has been open for a grand total of 23,717 minutes. wow. i might even shell out the $30 for it, it's good stuff.

		

